"state":1,"numComments":0,"cws":[],"tags":["games","game development"],"hasCohostPlus":true,"pinned":false,"commentsLocked":false,"sharesLocked":false,"blocks":[{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"One of the major reasons I'm not really in games these days is because I really have no idea how to do the work creatively and sustainably. My best so far seems to be \"hope my employer's stock keeps doing crazy things, then retire, live in a trailer on 40 acres of land, and blow it all on making a video game and\u002For survivalist farming\" (the Brian Bucklew strategy; Qud, which I love, exists because Brian had a successful startup doing something else.) I love my job, but I would still rather be making Game #3, which is in pre-production, or even working more on Dredmor and queueing up Dredmor II 3D: The Quest For More Money, you know? That's the thing I wanted to do since I was five."}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"I don't know how to do it any more, or how to do it sustainably as a 40 year old, and I'm incredibly saddened by this fact."}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"Maybe this is what it feels like to be Hayao Miyazaki."}}],"plainTextBody":"One of the major reasons I'm not really in games these days is because I really have no idea how to do the work creatively and sustainably. My best so far seems to be \"hope my employer's stock keeps doing crazy things, then retire, live in a trailer on 40 acres of land, and blow it all on making a video game and\u002For survivalist farming\" (the Brian Bucklew strategy; Qud, which I love, exists because Brian had a successful startup doing something else.) I love my job, but I would still rather be making Game #3, which is in pre-production, or even working more on Dredmor and queueing up Dredmor II 3D: The Quest For More Money, you know? That's the thing I wanted to do since I was five.\n\nI don't know how to do it any more, or how to do it sustainably as a 40 year old, and I'm incredibly saddened by this fact.\n\nMaybe this is what it feels like to be Hayao Miyazaki.","postingProject":{"projectId":11268,"handle":"egotists-club","displayName":"Egotists Club","dek":"","description":"“The Egotists’ Club is one of the most genial places in London. It is a place to which you may go when you want to tell that odd dream you had last night, or to announce what a good dentist you have discovered. You can write letters there if you like, and have the temperament of a Jane Austen, for there is no silence room, and it would be a breach of club manners to appear busy or absorbed when another member addresses you.” -- Dorothy L. Sayers, The Man With The Copper Fingers\r\n\r\n(Once again, opinions not those of my employers.)","avatarURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Favatar\u002F11268-91a99b96-9c78-44ce-a238-4318dfb61ba4-profile.jpg","avatarPreviewURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Favatar\u002F11268-91a99b96-9c78-44ce-a238-4318dfb61ba4-profile.jpg","headerURL":null,"headerPreviewURL":null,"privacy":"public","url":"","pronouns":"","flags":[],"avatarShape":"circle","loggedOutPostVisibility":"public","frequentlyUsedTags":[],"askSettings":{"enabled":true,"allowAnon":true,"requireLoggedInAnon":true},"contactCard":[],"deleteAfter":null,"isSelfProject":null},"shareTree":[],"numSharedComments":0,"relatedProjects":[],"singlePostPageUrl":"https:\u002F\u002Fcohost.org\u002Fegotists-club\u002Fpost\u002F4260228-one-of-the-major-rea","effectiveAdultContent":false,"isEditor":false,"hasAnyContributorMuted":false,"contributorBlockIncomingOrOutgoing":false,"postEditUrl":"https:\u002F\u002Fcohost.org\u002Fegotists-club\u002Fpost\u002F4260228-one-of-the-major-rea\u002Fedit","isLiked":false,"canShare":true,"canPublish":true,"limitedVisibilityReason":"none","astMap":{"spans":[{"startIndex":0,"endIndex":3,"ast":"{\"type\":\"root\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"One of the major reasons I'm not really in games these days is because I really have no idea how to do the work creatively and sustainably. My best so far seems to be \\\"hope my employer's stock keeps doing crazy things, then retire, live in a trailer on 40 acres of land, and blow it all on making a video game and\u002For survivalist farming\\\" (the Brian Bucklew strategy; Qud, which I love, exists because Brian had a successful startup doing something else.) I love my job, but I would still rather be making Game #3, which is in pre-production, or even working more on Dredmor and queueing up Dredmor II 3D: The Quest For More Money, you know? That's the thing I wanted to do since I was five.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":1,\"offset\":0},\"end\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":691,\"offset\":690}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":1,\"offset\":0},\"end\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":691,\"offset\":690}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"I don't know how to do it any more, or how to do it sustainably as a 40 year old, and I'm incredibly saddened by this fact.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":3,\"column\":1,\"offset\":692},\"end\":{\"line\":3,\"column\":124,\"offset\":815}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":3,\"column\":1,\"offset\":692},\"end\":{\"line\":3,\"column\":124,\"offset\":815}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"Maybe this is what it feels like to be Hayao Miyazaki.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":1,\"offset\":817},\"end\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":55,\"offset\":871}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":1,\"offset\":817},\"end\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":55,\"offset\":871}}}],\"data\":{\"quirksMode\":false},\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":1,\"offset\":0},\"end\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":55,\"offset\":871}}}"}],"readMoreIndex":null},"responseToAskId":null},{"postId":4260681,"headline":"Capitalism isn’t a snake that eats its own tail. It’s a fire that burns its forest down.","publishedAt":"2024-01-23T18:33:57.373Z","filename":"4260681-capitalism-isn-t-a-s","transparentShareOfPostId":null,"shareOfPostId":4260310,"state":1,"numComments":0,"cws":[],"tags":["games","games development","fuck capitalism"],"hasCohostPlus":false,"pinned":false,"commentsLocked":false,"sharesLocked":false,"blocks":[{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"“Infinite Growth” has been a driving goal in our economy since the Industrial Revolution, but the problem is that we’re trying to make this work within finite systems with limited resources. Of course many of these resources can recycle and renew themselves, but not in such a manner that allows it to do what capitalism wants it to do."}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"Games are no exception. Every year we want better graphics, bigger scales, greater content. Some people want those “infinite conversation trees” with “fully immersive open worlds”. Some people want those perfect, competitive games that you can hone your skills that will remain relevant and useful. Some people want those games that evolve and grow alongside you, and continue to change as the years pass. We want infinite growth not just in the companies that produce these games and the wealth they provide, but in the games themselves."}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"Procedural, automated systems are the current idea to make this possible— stories, characters, and literal entire planets to explore and experience; impossible to create by hand because of the scale but possible for a computer to generate. But the hand-made quality is never there, and we always notice. The AI Tech Bros are desperate for this scale of game, and see their tech as a glimmer of hope for this possibility, but it will never be what they want it to be."}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"Because infinite growth is impossible. Unsustainable. Once the system reaches those limitations, it will collapse. It will collapse absolutely. This has happened countless times throughout history. Time is a flat circle."}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"The current Video Games business model will collapse, because it’s built on such an incredibly bad foundation. The demands for product and productivity will continue to escalate, and the human backs these expectations are built upon will break. Even if the output of the automation systems were as good as many people want and claim them to be, it won’t be a solution because if the machine can print $100 bills the consumers and VCs will go “Okay but what it they printed $1000 bills?” There is no degree of scale people will be satisfied, and every system has limitations that will break them no matter how hard the executives ignore them."}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"So, when I read about the Games Industry collapsing above, I believe it. It makes sense. It is collapsing and it will burn itself down. But a burnt forest fertilizes and rubble can be reused. I’m confident that an end now means something new can come along, and while I hope we as people can find equilibriums with our limitations that satisfy and fulfill us, I also don’t know if we will."}},{"type":"markdown","markdown":{"content":"But for now, there are games that can be played and experienced, and people to support each other. Ape together strong and so forth."}}],"plainTextBody":"“Infinite Growth” has been a driving goal in our economy since the Industrial Revolution, but the problem is that we’re trying to make this work within finite systems with limited resources. Of course many of these resources can recycle and renew themselves, but not in such a manner that allows it to do what capitalism wants it to do.\n\nGames are no exception. Every year we want better graphics, bigger scales, greater content. Some people want those “infinite conversation trees” with “fully immersive open worlds”. Some people want those perfect, competitive games that you can hone your skills that will remain relevant and useful. Some people want those games that evolve and grow alongside you, and continue to change as the years pass. We want infinite growth not just in the companies that produce these games and the wealth they provide, but in the games themselves.\n\nProcedural, automated systems are the current idea to make this possible— stories, characters, and literal entire planets to explore and experience; impossible to create by hand because of the scale but possible for a computer to generate. But the hand-made quality is never there, and we always notice. The AI Tech Bros are desperate for this scale of game, and see their tech as a glimmer of hope for this possibility, but it will never be what they want it to be.\n\nBecause infinite growth is impossible. Unsustainable. Once the system reaches those limitations, it will collapse. It will collapse absolutely. This has happened countless times throughout history. Time is a flat circle.\n\nThe current Video Games business model will collapse, because it’s built on such an incredibly bad foundation. The demands for product and productivity will continue to escalate, and the human backs these expectations are built upon will break. Even if the output of the automation systems were as good as many people want and claim them to be, it won’t be a solution because if the machine can print $100 bills the consumers and VCs will go “Okay but what it they printed $1000 bills?” There is no degree of scale people will be satisfied, and every system has limitations that will break them no matter how hard the executives ignore them.\n\nSo, when I read about the Games Industry collapsing above, I believe it. It makes sense. It is collapsing and it will burn itself down. But a burnt forest fertilizes and rubble can be reused. I’m confident that an end now means something new can come along, and while I hope we as people can find equilibriums with our limitations that satisfy and fulfill us, I also don’t know if we will.\n\nBut for now, there are games that can be played and experienced, and people to support each other. Ape together strong and so forth.","postingProject":{"projectId":34693,"handle":"DVD-Player","displayName":"DVD Player","dek":"Writer, 3D Artist, Modder","description":"General creative dude with ADHD. Currently I write about working-class young adults who become magical girls and fight Literal Demon Capitalism.\r\n\r\nFollow me here nerds:\r\ndvd-player.bsky.social\r\nwww.tumblr.com\u002Fdisk-tray","avatarURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Favatar\u002F34693-30162ac0-1060-49e4-b67c-b7ee2741fbfe-profile.jpg","avatarPreviewURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Favatar\u002F34693-30162ac0-1060-49e4-b67c-b7ee2741fbfe-profile.jpg","headerURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Fheader\u002F34693-391568da-b306-49a0-8a18-19ccd5c6679a-profile.png","headerPreviewURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Fheader\u002F34693-391568da-b306-49a0-8a18-19ccd5c6679a-profile.png","privacy":"public","url":"https:\u002F\u002Ftapas.io\u002Fseries\u002FBusiness-Magical\u002Finfo","pronouns":"He\u002FHim","flags":[],"avatarShape":"roundrect","loggedOutPostVisibility":"public","frequentlyUsedTags":[],"askSettings":{"enabled":true,"allowAnon":true,"requireLoggedInAnon":true},"contactCard":[],"deleteAfter":null,"isSelfProject":null},"shareTree":[],"numSharedComments":0,"relatedProjects":[],"singlePostPageUrl":"https:\u002F\u002Fcohost.org\u002FDVD-Player\u002Fpost\u002F4260681-capitalism-isn-t-a-s","effectiveAdultContent":false,"isEditor":false,"hasAnyContributorMuted":false,"contributorBlockIncomingOrOutgoing":false,"postEditUrl":"https:\u002F\u002Fcohost.org\u002FDVD-Player\u002Fpost\u002F4260681-capitalism-isn-t-a-s\u002Fedit","isLiked":false,"canShare":true,"canPublish":true,"limitedVisibilityReason":"none","astMap":{"spans":[{"startIndex":0,"endIndex":7,"ast":"{\"type\":\"root\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"“Infinite Growth” has been a driving goal in our economy since the Industrial Revolution, but the problem is that we’re trying to make this work within finite systems with limited resources. Of course many of these resources can recycle and renew themselves, but not in such a manner that allows it to do what capitalism wants it to do.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":1,\"offset\":0},\"end\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":337,\"offset\":336}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":1,\"offset\":0},\"end\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":337,\"offset\":336}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"Games are no exception. Every year we want better graphics, bigger scales, greater content. Some people want those “infinite conversation trees” with “fully immersive open worlds”. Some people want those perfect, competitive games that you can hone your skills that will remain relevant and useful. Some people want those games that evolve and grow alongside you, and continue to change as the years pass. We want infinite growth not just in the companies that produce these games and the wealth they provide, but in the games themselves.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":3,\"column\":1,\"offset\":338},\"end\":{\"line\":3,\"column\":539,\"offset\":876}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":3,\"column\":1,\"offset\":338},\"end\":{\"line\":3,\"column\":539,\"offset\":876}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"Procedural, automated systems are the current idea to make this possible— stories, characters, and literal entire planets to explore and experience; impossible to create by hand because of the scale but possible for a computer to generate. But the hand-made quality is never there, and we always notice. The AI Tech Bros are desperate for this scale of game, and see their tech as a glimmer of hope for this possibility, but it will never be what they want it to be.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":1,\"offset\":878},\"end\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":467,\"offset\":1344}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":1,\"offset\":878},\"end\":{\"line\":5,\"column\":467,\"offset\":1344}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"Because infinite growth is impossible. Unsustainable. Once the system reaches those limitations, it will collapse. It will collapse absolutely. This has happened countless times throughout history. Time is a flat circle.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":7,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1346},\"end\":{\"line\":7,\"column\":221,\"offset\":1566}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":7,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1346},\"end\":{\"line\":7,\"column\":221,\"offset\":1566}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"The current Video Games business model will collapse, because it’s built on such an incredibly bad foundation. The demands for product and productivity will continue to escalate, and the human backs these expectations are built upon will break. Even if the output of the automation systems were as good as many people want and claim them to be, it won’t be a solution because if the machine can print $100 bills the consumers and VCs will go “Okay but what it they printed $1000 bills?” There is no degree of scale people will be satisfied, and every system has limitations that will break them no matter how hard the executives ignore them.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":9,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1568},\"end\":{\"line\":9,\"column\":642,\"offset\":2209}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":9,\"column\":1,\"offset\":1568},\"end\":{\"line\":9,\"column\":642,\"offset\":2209}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"So, when I read about the Games Industry collapsing above, I believe it. It makes sense. It is collapsing and it will burn itself down. But a burnt forest fertilizes and rubble can be reused. I’m confident that an end now means something new can come along, and while I hope we as people can find equilibriums with our limitations that satisfy and fulfill us, I also don’t know if we will.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":11,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2211},\"end\":{\"line\":11,\"column\":390,\"offset\":2600}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":11,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2211},\"end\":{\"line\":11,\"column\":390,\"offset\":2600}}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"\\n\"},{\"type\":\"element\",\"tagName\":\"p\",\"properties\":{},\"children\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"value\":\"But for now, there are games that can be played and experienced, and people to support each other. Ape together strong and so forth.\",\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":13,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2602},\"end\":{\"line\":13,\"column\":133,\"offset\":2734}}}],\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":13,\"column\":1,\"offset\":2602},\"end\":{\"line\":13,\"column\":133,\"offset\":2734}}}],\"data\":{\"quirksMode\":false},\"position\":{\"start\":{\"line\":1,\"column\":1,\"offset\":0},\"end\":{\"line\":13,\"column\":133,\"offset\":2734}}}"}],"readMoreIndex":null},"responseToAskId":null},{"postId":4261430,"headline":"All of this","publishedAt":"2024-01-23T19:57:13.470Z","filename":"4261430-all-of-this","transparentShareOfPostId":null,"shareOfPostId":4261265,"state":1,"numComments":1,"cws":[],"tags":[],"hasCohostPlus":false,"pinned":false,"commentsLocked":false,"sharesLocked":false,"blocks":