iv><a href="https://twitter.com/mokkograd" class="text-mango" rel="me nofollow noopener" target="_blank">twitter.com/mokkograd</a></div></div><div class="order-3 col-span-1 mb-16 lg:order-none lg:col-span-2"><!--$--><div class="mt-4 flex flex-col gap-4"><div data-view="post-preview" data-testid="post-4263466" data-postid="4263466" class="grid  w-full gap-x-6 gap-y-2"><article data-theme="both" class="co-themed-box co-post-box"><header class="co-thread-header"><div class="flex min-w-0 flex-1 flex-row flex-wrap items-center gap-2 leading-none"><div class="flex-0 mask relative aspect-square h-8 w-8 lg:hidden inline-block"><img src="https://staging.cohostcdn.org/avatar/7783-5df1d46c-b45a-414f-86a6-7932187d15b4-profile.png?dpr=2&amp;width=80&amp;height=80&amp;fit=cover&amp;auto=webp" class="mask mask-squircle h-full w-full object-cover" alt="MOKKA"/></div><a rel="author" href="https://cohost.org/MOKKA" class="co-project-display-name max-w-full flex-shrink truncate font-atkinson font-bold hover:underline" title="Eric">Eric</a><a href="https://cohost.org/MOKKA" class="co-project-handle font-atkinson font-normal hover:underline">@<!-- -->MOKKA<!-- --></a><time dateTime="2024-01-23T23:48:06.193Z" class="block flex-none text-xs tabular-nums text-gray-500" title="Tue, Jan 23, 2024, 11:48 PM"><a href="https://cohost.org/MOKKA/post/4263466-back-in-early-2021" class="hover:underline">1/23/2024, 11:48 PM</a></time><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true" class="co-project-display-name h-5 w-5"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4.755 10.059a7.5 7.5 0 0112.548-3.364l1.903 1.903h-3.183a.75.75 0 100 1.5h4.992a.75.75 0 00.75-.75V4.356a.75.75 0 00-1.5 0v3.18l-1.9-1.9A9 9 0 003.306 9.67a.75.75 0 101.45.388zm15.408 3.352a.75.75 0 00-.919.53 7.5 7.5 0 01-12.548 3.364l-1.902-1.903h3.183a.75.75 0 000-1.5H2.984a.75.75 0 00-.75.75v4.992a.75.75 0 001.5 0v-3.18l1.9 1.9a9 9 0 0015.059-4.035.75.75 0 00-.53-.918z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg><div class="flex-0 mask relative aspect-square h-8 w-8 lg:hidden inline-block"><img src="https://staging.cohostcdn.org/avatar/58038-8127b2ea-331a-4b02-a2ba-70928198b5e8-profile.jpeg?dpr=2&amp;width=80&amp;height=80&amp;fit=cover&amp;auto=webp" class="mask mask-circle h-full w-full object-cover" alt="danielleri"/></div><a href="https://cohost.org/danielleri" class="co-project-handle font-atkinson font-normal hover:underline">@<!-- -->danielleri<!-- --></a></div><button id="headlessui-menu-button-:Rcdaiet:" type="button" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-headlessui-state=""><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true" class="co-action-button h-6 w-6 transition-transform ui-open:rotate-90"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6.75 12a.75.75 0 11-1.5 0 .75.75 0 011.5 0zM12.75 12a.75.75 0 11-1.5 0 .75.75 0 011.5 0zM18.75 12a.75.75 0 11-1.5 0 .75.75 0 011.5 0z"></path></svg></button></header><hr class="co-hairline"/><div><div id="post-4256715" data-testid="post-body-4256715" class="relative -top-20"></div><div class="co-post-header flex flex-row flex-wrap items-center gap-2 px-3 py-2"><div class="flex-0 mask relative aspect-square h-8 w-8  inline-block"><img src="https://staging.cohostcdn.org/avatar/503-9d77a9c6-e89f-4abb-b9a8-b42b388ab3b7-profile.png?dpr=2&amp;width=80&amp;height=80&amp;fit=cover&amp;auto=webp" class="mask mask-squircle h-full w-full object-cover" alt="prophetgoddess"/></div><a rel="author" href="https://cohost.org/prophetgoddess" class="co-project-display-name max-w-full flex-shrink truncate font-atkinson font-bold hover:underline" title="cass">cass</a><a href="https://cohost.org/prophetgoddess" class="co-project-handle font-atkinson font-normal hover:underline">@<!-- -->prophetgoddess<!-- --></a><time dateTime="2024-01-23T05:16:30.470Z" class="block flex-none text-xs tabular-nums text-gray-500" title="Tue, Jan 23, 2024, 5:16 AM"><a href="https://cohost.org/prophetgoddess/post/4256715-video-games-are-so-w" class="hover:underline">1/23/2024, 5:16 AM</a></time></div><div><div><div class="flex w-full flex-row p-3"><a href="https://cohost.org/prophetgoddess/post/4256715-video-games-are-so-w" class="co-prose prose flex-grow self-center break-words hover:underline"><h3>video games are so washed dude</h3></a></div><div class=" relative overflow-hidden supports-[overflow:clip]:overflow-clip isolate co-contain-paint" data-post-body="true" data-testid="post-body"><div class="co-prose prose my-4 overflow-hidden break-words px-3"><p>i honestly fear for the entire medium at this point. there were 9,000 layoffs in the game industry last year, and there have now been 3000 just <!-- --><em>this month<!-- --></em>. it doesn&#x27;t seem like it&#x27;s going to stop. and that&#x27;s just layoffs that were announced as layoffs, not any of the other ways that companies force employees to quit without having to fire them (return-to-office policies, moving people&#x27;s jobs to faraway cities, etc)<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>and outside AAA, nobody is funding indie games anymore. publishers are either not taking pitches at all, or won&#x27;t take pitches for games that cost less than a million dollars. everyone i know, from new indies looking to pitch their first commercial project, to established developers with several hits under their belt is struggling to get anyone to even listen to them. everyone, from AAA down, is putting all their eggs into the biggest possible baskets to guarantee hits.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>and this has an effect on smaller games that are made <!-- --><em>without<!-- --></em> publisher funding. for one, it&#x27;s harder than ever to do that: if you have the skills to make a video game and aren&#x27;t a professional developer there&#x27;s a good chance you just got laid off from your job in tech too, because that whole industry is collapsing. everything is more expensive than it used to be. and the big companies spending more and more on their &quot;indie&quot; projects just makes anything that&#x27;s not that level of quality look like a cash grab.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>i keep thinking about dave the diver, a game developed and published by nexon, a billion dollar company, a giant in the korean gaming market, getting called an indie game by morons too stupid to realize that a game isn&#x27;t indie just because it has pixel art graphics!<!-- --><sup>1<!-- --></sup></p>
<!-- --><p>that&#x27;s what we&#x27;re up against. massive companies spending millions of dollars on huge projects and disguising them as indie games. i know it&#x27;s cliche to hate it, but i&#x27;m so sick of the whole &quot;shorter games worse graphics etc etc&quot; bullshit because it&#x27;s not true. you don&#x27;t want that. you&#x27;re lying to me, and i hate being lied to.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>i feel like i&#x27;ve wasted my life. i spent all this time nodding and cheering when people said that video games could be more, do more, that there was room in the industry for all kinds of freaks and weirdos. i devoted my life to proving them right, i spent years honing my craft and then those people turn around and say &quot;fortnite&#x27;s actually really good, they got goku in there now.&quot; dave the diver nominated for best independent game. &quot;you should really take genshin impact seriously, a lot of people like it.&quot; fuck off. i am so sick of wasting my time trying to impress these losers. i want so badly to make the video games that i think would really matter to people, and it&#x27;s just a total waste of time. they don&#x27;t care. you don&#x27;t care. nobody cares.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><hr/>
<!-- --><p>1:  (and, let&#x27;s be honest: they don&#x27;t know or care what nexon is or how big of a deal they are because they&#x27;re racist and nexon is korean)<!-- --></p></div></div></div></div><hr class="co-hairline"/></div><div><div id="post-4259568" data-testid="post-body-4259568" class="relative -top-20"></div><div class="co-post-header flex flex-row flex-wrap items-center gap-2 px-3 py-2"><div class="flex-0 mask relative aspect-square h-8 w-8  inline-block"><img src="https://staging.cohostcdn.org/avatar/3298-780b1ee8-34f5-48d6-a873-26dc7dfa5e05-profile.png?dpr=2&amp;width=80&amp;height=80&amp;fit=cover&amp;auto=webp" class="mask mask-squircle h-full w-full object-cover" alt="eniko"/></div><a rel="author" href="https://cohost.org/eniko" class="co-project-display-name max-w-full flex-shrink truncate font-atkinson font-bold hover:underline" title="Eniko | Kitsune Tails out now!">Eniko | Kitsune Tails out now!</a><a href="https://cohost.org/eniko" class="co-project-handle font-atkinson font-normal hover:underline">@<!-- -->eniko<!-- --></a><time dateTime="2024-01-23T16:15:20.496Z" class="block flex-none text-xs tabular-nums text-gray-500" title="Tue, Jan 23, 2024, 4:15 PM"><a href="https://cohost.org/eniko/post/4259568-nobody-is-funding" class="hover:underline">1/23/2024, 4:15 PM</a></time></div><div><div><div class=" relative overflow-hidden supports-[overflow:clip]:overflow-clip isolate co-contain-paint" data-post-body="true" data-testid="post-body"><div class="co-prose prose my-4 overflow-hidden break-words px-3"><blockquote>
<!-- --><p>nobody is funding indie games anymore. publishers are either not taking pitches at all, or won&#x27;t take pitches for games that cost less than a million dollars<!-- --></p>
<!-- --></blockquote>
<!-- --><p>this has been my experience the past few years too. and for the uninitiated, what taking a million in venture capital funding does (because lets face it, most indie-funding publishers that can toss out millions of dollars have some shadowy VC behind their friendly outward facing owners) is they fucking own your ass. bet on that million dollars being the only money you ever see out of that deal, even if the game becomes a hit, because the people who gave you funding can and will cut themselves a blank check for &quot;expenses&quot; just so they&#x27;ll never have to pay you the % they promised since they magically never recoup their losses<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>not only that, you can&#x27;t make a sequel with better terms either. they&#x27;ll want &quot;right of first refusal&quot; which basically says you have to give them the opportunity to work with you first on sequals or spinoffs or whatever, and if you can&#x27;t come to an agreement (i.e. you don&#x27;t consent to whatever shitty deal they give you) they can sue your ass. and hey, remember how they have a shadowy VC funding them and you got nothing out of your hit game?<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>plus, like. a lot of indie games don&#x27;t <!-- --><em>need<!-- --></em> a million fucking dollars in funding. they need 250k, or 100k, or even 50k or less to finish. but they&#x27;re not interested in that at all. that&#x27;s not in their &quot;throw big money at lots of things and some will become a smash hit and pay back orders of magnitude more&quot; playbook<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>and this then creates a culture of haves and have-nots. we&#x27;re making kitsune tails on a shoe string budget (mostly me and my partner slowly whittling away all our assets until we&#x27;ve got basically nothing left) and we&#x27;re competing with &quot;indies&quot; that have development budget in the multiple millions. of course we can&#x27;t make a game of the same size, scope, and polish level with 0.01% of the budget. and that&#x27;s not even going into the BS that is multi billion dollar multinationals trying to get in on it by being like &quot;oh hey look at this cute <!-- --><em>indie<!-- --></em> game we made&quot;<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>things are fucked<!-- --></p></div></div></div></div><hr class="co-hairline"/></div><div><div id="post-4260228" data-testid="post-body-4260228" class="relative -top-20"></div><div class="co-post-header flex flex-row flex-wrap items-center gap-2 px-3 py-2"><div class="flex-0 mask relative aspect-square h-8 w-8  inline-block"><img src="https://staging.cohostcdn.org/avatar/11268-91a99b96-9c78-44ce-a238-4318dfb61ba4-profile.jpg?dpr=2&amp;width=80&amp;height=80&amp;fit=cover&amp;auto=webp" class="mask mask-circle h-full w-full object-cover" alt="egotists-club"/></div><a rel="author" href="https://cohost.org/egotists-club" class="co-project-display-name max-w-full flex-shrink truncate font-atkinson font-bold hover:underline" title="Egotists Club">Egotists Club</a><a href="https://cohost.org/egotists-club" class="co-project-handle font-atkinson font-normal hover:underline">@<!-- -->egotists-club<!-- --></a><time dateTime="2024-01-23T17:42:46.744Z" class="block flex-none text-xs tabular-nums text-gray-500" title="Tue, Jan 23, 2024, 5:42 PM"><a href="https://cohost.org/egotists-club/post/4260228-one-of-the-major-rea" class="hover:underline">1/23/2024, 5:42 PM</a></time></div><div><div><div class=" relative overflow-hidden supports-[overflow:clip]:overflow-clip isolate co-contain-paint" data-post-body="true" data-testid="post-body"><div class="co-prose prose my-4 overflow-hidden break-words px-3"><p>One of the major reasons I&#x27;m not really in games these days is because I really have no idea how to do the work creatively and sustainably. My best so far seems to be &quot;hope my employer&#x27;s stock keeps doing crazy things, then retire, live in a trailer on 40 acres of land, and blow it all on making a video game and/or survivalist farming&quot; (the Brian Bucklew strategy; Qud, which I love, exists because Brian had a successful startup doing something else.) I love my job, but I would still rather be making Game #3, which is in pre-production, or even working more on Dredmor and queueing up Dredmor II 3D: The Quest For More Money, you know? That&#x27;s the thing I wanted to do since I was five.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>I don&#x27;t know how to do it any more, or how to do it sustainably as a 40 year old, and I&#x27;m incredibly saddened by this fact.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>Maybe this is what it feels like to be Hayao Miyazaki.<!-- --></p></div></div><div class="w-full max-w-full p-3"><div class="co-tags relative w-full overflow-y-hidden break-words leading-none max-h-[60px]"><div><a class="mr-2 inline-block text-sm hover:underline  " href="https://cohost.org/MOKKA/tagged/games">#<!-- -->games<!-- --></a><a class="mr-2 inline-block text-sm hover:underline  " href="https://cohost.org/MOKKA/tagged/game%20development">#<!-- -->game development<!-- --></a></div><div class="absolute bottom-0 right-2 flex h-5"><span class="co-from-body inline-block h-full bg-gradient-to-l pl-4"></span><button class="co-tags co-opaque inline-block cursor-pointer text-sm font-bold hover:underline">see all</button></div></div></div></div></div><hr class="co-hairline"/></div><div><div id="post-4260681" data-testid="post-body-4260681" class="relative -top-20"></div><div class="co-post-header flex flex-row flex-wrap items-center gap-2 px-3 py-2"><div class="flex-0 mask relative aspect-square h-8 w-8  inline-block"><img src="https://staging.cohostcdn.org/avatar/34693-30162ac0-1060-49e4-b67c-b7ee2741fbfe-profile.jpg?dpr=2&amp;width=80&amp;height=80&amp;fit=cover&amp;auto=webp" class="mask mask-roundrect h-full w-full object-cover" alt="DVD-Player"/></div><a rel="author" href="https://cohost.org/DVD-Player" class="co-project-display-name max-w-full flex-shrink truncate font-atkinson font-bold hover:underline" title="DVD Player">DVD Player</a><a href="https://cohost.org/DVD-Player" class="co-project-handle font-atkinson font-normal hover:underline">@<!-- -->DVD-Player<!-- --></a><time dateTime="2024-01-23T18:33:57.373Z" class="block flex-none text-xs tabular-nums text-gray-500" title="Tue, Jan 23, 2024, 6:33 PM"><a href="https://cohost.org/DVD-Player/post/4260681-capitalism-isn-t-a-s" class="hover:underline">1/23/2024, 6:33 PM</a></time></div><div><div><div class="flex w-full flex-row p-3"><a href="https://cohost.org/DVD-Player/post/4260681-capitalism-isn-t-a-s" class="co-prose prose flex-grow self-center break-words hover:underline"><h3>Capitalism isn’t a snake that eats its own tail. It’s a fire that burns its forest down.</h3></a></div><div class=" relative overflow-hidden supports-[overflow:clip]:overflow-clip isolate co-contain-paint" data-post-body="true" data-testid="post-body"><div class="co-prose prose my-4 overflow-hidden break-words px-3"><p>“Infinite Growth” has been a driving goal in our economy since the Industrial Revolution, but the problem is that we’re trying to make this work within finite systems with limited resources. Of course many of these resources can recycle and renew themselves, but not in such a manner that allows it to do what capitalism wants it to do.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>Games are no exception. Every year we want better graphics, bigger scales, greater content. Some people want those “infinite conversation trees” with “fully immersive open worlds”. Some people want those perfect, competitive games that you can hone your skills that will remain relevant and useful. Some people want those games that evolve and grow alongside you, and continue to change as the years pass. We want infinite growth not just in the companies that produce these games and the wealth they provide, but in the games themselves.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>Procedural, automated systems are the current idea to make this possible— stories, characters, and literal entire planets to explore and experience; impossible to create by hand because of the scale but possible for a computer to generate. But the hand-made quality is never there, and we always notice. The AI Tech Bros are desperate for this scale of game, and see their tech as a glimmer of hope for this possibility, but it will never be what they want it to be.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>Because infinite growth is impossible. Unsustainable. Once the system reaches those limitations, it will collapse. It will collapse absolutely. This has happened countless times throughout history. Time is a flat circle.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>The current Video Games business model will collapse, because it’s built on such an incredibly bad foundation. The demands for product and productivity will continue to escalate, and the human backs these expectations are built upon will break. Even if the output of the automation systems were as good as many people want and claim them to be, it won’t be a solution because if the machine can print $100 bills the consumers and VCs will go “Okay but what it they printed $1000 bills?” There is no degree of scale people will be satisfied, and every system has limitations that will break them no matter how hard the executives ignore them.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>So, when I read about the Games Industry collapsing above, I believe it. It makes sense. It is collapsing and it will burn itself down. But a burnt forest fertilizes and rubble can be reused. I’m confident that an end now means something new can come along, and while I hope we as people can find equilibriums with our limitations that satisfy and fulfill us, I also don’t know if we will.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>But for now, there are games that can be played and experienced, and people to support each other. Ape together strong and so forth.<!-- --></p></div></div><div class="w-full max-w-full p-3"><div class="co-tags relative w-full overflow-y-hidden break-words leading-none max-h-[60px]"><div><a class="mr-2 inline-block text-sm hover:underline  " href="https://cohost.org/MOKKA/tagged/games">#<!-- -->games<!-- --></a><a class="mr-2 inline-block text-sm hover:underline  " href="https://cohost.org/MOKKA/tagged/games%20development">#<!-- -->games development<!-- --></a><a class="mr-2 inline-block text-sm hover:underline  " href="https://cohost.org/MOKKA/tagged/fuck%20capitalism">#<!-- -->fuck capitalism<!-- --></a></div><div class="absolute bottom-0 right-2 flex h-5"><span class="co-from-body inline-block h-full bg-gradient-to-l pl-4"></span><button class="co-tags co-opaque inline-block cursor-pointer text-sm font-bold hover:underline">see all</button></div></div></div></div></div><hr class="co-hairline"/></div><div><div id="post-4261430" data-testid="post-body-4261430" class="relative -top-20"></div><div class="co-post-header flex flex-row flex-wrap items-center gap-2 px-3 py-2"><div class="flex-0 mask relative aspect-square h-8 w-8  inline-block"><img src="https://staging.cohostcdn.org/avatar/58038-8127b2ea-331a-4b02-a2ba-70928198b5e8-profile.jpeg?dpr=2&amp;width=80&amp;height=80&amp;fit=cover&amp;auto=webp" class="mask mask-circle h-full w-full object-cover" alt="danielleri"/></div><a href="https://cohost.org/danielleri" class="co-project-handle font-atkinson font-normal hover:underline">@<!-- -->danielleri<!-- --></a><time dateTime="2024-01-23T19:57:13.470Z" class="block flex-none text-xs tabular-nums text-gray-500" title="Tue, Jan 23, 2024, 7:57 PM"><a href="https://cohost.org/danielleri/post/4261430-all-of-this" class="hover:underline">1/23/2024, 7:57 PM</a></time></div><div><div><div class="flex w-full flex-row p-3"><a href="https://cohost.org/danielleri/post/4261430-all-of-this" class="co-prose prose flex-grow self-center break-words hover:underline"><h3>All of this</h3></a></div><div class=" relative overflow-hidden supports-[overflow:clip]:overflow-clip isolate co-contain-paint" data-post-body="true" data-testid="post-body"><div class="co-prose prose my-4 overflow-hidden break-words px-3"><p>I just want to co-sign and nod and scream and have everyone read these thoughts (except the part about brain dead journalists, which, BELIEVE ME, I understand some anger directed at game journalists -- what&#x27;s left of us -- but things are so, so SO dire in this corner of the space that uh, bad things come out of it).<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>I had one of my game design students reach out to me asking what they can do to try and find a career in the industry in the midst of this and I am currently trying to think of how to answer them.<!-- --></p></div></div></div></div><hr class="co-hairline"/></div><div><div id="post-4263466" data-testid="post-body-4263466" class="relative -top-20"></div><div class="co-post-header flex flex-row flex-wrap items-center gap-2 px-3 py-2"><div class="flex-0 mask relative aspect-square h-8 w-8  inline-block"><img src="https://staging.cohostcdn.org/avatar/7783-5df1d46c-b45a-414f-86a6-7932187d15b4-profile.png?dpr=2&amp;width=80&amp;height=80&amp;fit=cover&amp;auto=webp" class="mask mask-squircle h-full w-full object-cover" alt="MOKKA"/></div><a rel="author" href="https://cohost.org/MOKKA" class="co-project-display-name max-w-full flex-shrink truncate font-atkinson font-bold hover:underline" title="Eric">Eric</a><a href="https://cohost.org/MOKKA" class="co-project-handle font-atkinson font-normal hover:underline">@<!-- -->MOKKA<!-- --></a><time dateTime="2024-01-23T23:48:06.193Z" class="block flex-none text-xs tabular-nums text-gray-500" title="Tue, Jan 23, 2024, 11:48 PM"><a href="https://cohost.org/MOKKA/post/4263466-back-in-early-2021" class="hover:underline">1/23/2024, 11:48 PM</a></time></div><div><div><div class="flex w-full flex-row p-3"><a href="https://cohost.org/MOKKA/post/4263466-back-in-early-2021" class="co-prose prose flex-grow self-center break-words hover:underline"><h3>Back in early 2021, after reading some Engels,</h3></a></div><div class=" relative overflow-hidden supports-[overflow:clip]:overflow-clip isolate co-contain-paint" data-post-body="true" data-testid="post-body"><div class="co-prose prose my-4 overflow-hidden break-words px-3"><p><a href="https://mokkograd.net/posts/2021-02-18-Individualsit%20production%20under%20capitalism" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">I wrote this blogpost<!-- --></a> about how his descriptions of the early shift from individualised production of goods (=one person works to create something) to socialised production (=a lot of people work together to create something) under Capitalism reminded me how it feels to make games on your own, while having to sell them right next to AAA titles:<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>I&#x27;m not sharing this to do a &quot;go and read some theory, friends&quot;, but more because I&#x27;m really tired of seeing people try to fight this stuff on their own, when the only real way through this, is when we pool our resources and knowledge together.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>I want for all of us to be in a better position to make the things that we want to make, and most of the things that would be needed for that are not possible without major political shifts across the entire world. However, I do believe that we all can do more to help each other, to pool our resources, to share knowledge. I&#x27;m very much to blame here as well, not because I don&#x27;t trust people, but because talking to them makes me scared and I also have this fundamental belief that I don&#x27;t have anything of value to offer to anyone. But I would like to help, as I would like for all of us to help each other.<!-- --></p>
<!-- --><p>(Apologies if this reads incoherent, it&#x27;s almost 1am over here and I was supposed to go to bed when I saw these posts)<!-- --></p></div></div></div></div></div><hr class="co-hairline"/><footer class="co-thread-footer w-full max-w-full rounded-b-lg p-3"><div class="flex justify-between align-middle"><div class="w-max flex-none"><a href="https://cohost.org/MOKKA/post/4263466-back-in-early-2021#comments" class="text-sm hover:underline">0 comments<!-- --> + 10 on shared posts<!-- --></a></div><div class="flex items-center justify-end gap-3"><a href="https://cohost.org/Corncycle/post/compose?shareOfPostId=4263466" title="share this post as Corncycle"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true" class="h-6 w-6 co-action-button "><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M16.023 9.348h4.992v-.001M2.985 19.644v-4.992m0 0h4.992m-4.993 0l3.181 3.183a8.25 8.25 0 0013.803-3.7M4.031 9.865a8.25 8.25 0 0113.803-3.7l3.181 3.182m0-4.991v4.99"></path></svg></a><button class="w-6 h-6 pointer relative" title="unlike this post as Corncycle"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true" class="w-6 h-6 pointer absolute top-0 left-0 text-cherry visible"><path d="M11.645 20.91l-.007-.003-.022-.012a15.247 15.247 0 01-.383-.218 25.18 25.18 0 01-4.244-3.17C4.688 15.36 2.25 12.174 2.25 8.25 2.25 5.322 4.714 3 7.688 3A5.5 5.5 0 0112 5.052 5.5 5.5 0 0116.313 3c2.973 0 5.437 2.322 5.437 5.25 0 3.925-2.438 7.111-4.739 9.256a25.175 25.175 0 01-4.244 3.17 15.247 15.247 0 01-.383.219l-.022.012-.007.004-.003.001a.752.752 0 01-.704 0l-.003-.001z"></path></svg><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true" class="w-6 h-6 pointer absolute top-0 left-0 co-action-button invisible"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M21 8.25c0-2.485-2.09